The paper deals with the identification of macroscopic partial differential equations (PDEs) from microscopic observations using machine learning algorithms. This falls under the category of computational mathematics (cs.MS) as well as machine learning (cs.LG). The use of PDEs also suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also deals with the modeling of physicochemical processes, which could fall under the category of scientific computing (cs.SI) or computational engineering (cs.CE).
